The paper deals with a fundamental distributed problem in the SINR model for radio transmission, which is a topic of interest in several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on wireless networks and the use of the SINR model suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with distributed algorithms, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new technique for achieving dilution without knowledge of physical coordinates, which could place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
